zur mittelhochdeutschen Phraseologie, das sich mit einer bewusst allgemeinverständlich gehaltenen Beschreibungssprache auch an die mediävistischen Nachbarwissenschaften und jeden am Mittelalter Interessierten wendet.  aThe Phraseological Dictionary of Middle High German contains phrasemes, i.e., proverbs, idioms, formulaic greeting and farewell expressions, imprecations, standardized pairings (like 'good and bad'), and other firmly established word-combinations, arranged in alphabetical order under different headings. The material is drawn from several hundred texts dating from the period 1050-1350, Minnesang, heroic epics, Arthurian romance, non-fictional literature, etc. The dictionary proper is preceded by a study on the identification, classification, and lexicographic description of established word-combinations in historical texts.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aGerman languageyMiddle High German, 1050-1500vDictionaries. 0aGerman languageyMiddle High German, 1050-1500xPhraseology. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Linguistics and Semiotics 2000 - 2014z9783110636970oZDB-23-DLS08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2006z9783110277128oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET LINGUISTIK UND LITERATURWISSENSCHAFT  2006z9783110276893oZDB-23-DGA0 cprintz978348431264740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311094588140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110945881423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110945881/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGAb2006  aZDB-23-DGGb2006  aZDB-23-DLSc2000d2014